Description: Polish Forums is a website providing information on Poland and Polish communities.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: One thing that many people say about the internet is that is brings people from all over the world together. That's true, of course, but there's something else it can do, too - it can help people maintain links to their own country as they travel, study or work abroad, or even after they've emigrated. PolishForums.com is an online resource for foreign people and Poles wherever they are, and also welcomes anyone who's planning to travel to Poland or is interested in learning the language. Basic membership is free and gives access to all the facilities of the forum, although premium memberships are also available. As the name suggests, the heart of Polish Forums are the forums themselves. On the home page you'll find a category button with an impressive list of forum categories to choose from. Everything is covered, from news and current affairs  through sub forums for Poles living in other regions to food and drink and even guides on how to celebrate holidays in Poland. If you're looking for basic language lessons or free translations you'll find sections to help you out. There are also some extremely useful resources - more sub forums give members opportunities to search for or offer jobs and housing, find pen-pals or arrange events. PolishForums has been running since 2005, so almost everything relating to Poland has been discussed at some time. The site provides a searchable archive to help you track down exactly what you're looking for. If you can't find it, all you have to do is create a new thread and ask; the members are extremely helpful and somebody will be along with an answer soon! There's a lively community, too, so something interesting is always going on. If you enjoy your free membership and want to gain some extra benefits you can sign up for a gold membership. You can choose your own annual fee, and in return you get to view the forum without any ads, a larger inbox and the ability to see who's online. For higher fees you can add a custom signature and even a free lifetime VIP membership to a related site about Polish Women. If you're Polish and want to keep in touch, or if you have an interest in Poland, PolishForums.com is exactly what you're looking for.
Industry Groups: Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Real Estate, Travel and Tourism

Description: Innovative consumer electronics.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Our first product SoundBrake is a device that allows you to be isolated and immersed in your headphones, yet still be able to clearly hear important outside sounds. SoundBrake fits between your headphones and audio player. It listens to your surroundings while you listen to your audio and instantly streams in outside sounds to your headphones only when they're above your normal background noise level. This allows you to be aware of sounds like a door knock, phone call, announcement, car honk, or someone trying to get your attention. It provides the safety benefit of being aware of your surroundings while you're isolated in headphones.  SoundBrake can be used with any headphones and audio player, such as a laptop, computer, smartphone, or tablet. You can also use SoundBrake with Bluetooth headphones using a standalone Bluetooth module. SoundBrake is great for using at home, work, and in the outdoors. It is especially useful for video gamers and people using virtual reality systems because they are also visually isolated.

Description: Shustir is an online business portal that enables businesses to create an online storefront that showcases their products.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Shustir is an online business portal in which local, small business can create an online "storefront," showcasing products sold, ratings, improving internet search visibility, and providing some e-Commerce functionality.  Shustir gives local retailers, service businesses, consultants and start-ups instant, new power to market themselves on the web. That kind of power has been in short supply - until now. Forty-four percent of small business owners don't have a web site. And many who do have a virtual cabin in the woods - a nice place that's tough to find. That's a shame, since 92 percent of regularly online consumers surveyed said web research led them to buy something locally. (Source: WebVisible/Nielsen Online.) Shustir member businesses can log on anytime to add or edit content and photos, respond to a consumer's comment or question, update their blog - even upload a virtual video tour of their store or products. E-commerce functionality is available at a modest $25 monthly fee. A small business on Shustir is instantly more visible to consumers through Shustir's own searchable marketplace, and through Google and other major search engines. Shustir handles the optimization - often too costly for a standalone small business site, but the most critical element in getting found via search, or not.

Description: CarCaddy is a website based business that seeks to link customers who are interested in trading in their vehicle with dealerships
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: CarCaddy is a website based business that seeks to link customers who are interested in trading in their vehicle with dealerships that are interested in purchasing their car for trade-in value. Dealers that sign up with CarCaddy will have the ability to bid, for up to five days, on a member customer's trade-in vehicle. The premise behind the site is for member customers to get the most value for their trade-in vehicle and for dealers to gain a car for their inventor and, a lead on a new customer. For these reasons, dealers will be incentivized to sign up with CarCaddy. Dealers are also able to avoid the exuberant fees associated with purchasing cars at auction for their inventory.     Initially, we will offer dealers a free membership for six months, allowing full access to CarCaddy services. After six months, dealers will be charged $695 per month. Customers who sign up will not be charged any fee for the service.    A future service planned on CarCaddy includes the ability to enter preferences for a new car purchase. This information will then be sent to member dealers who will "bid" on selling a customer a car at the lowest price. Additional services planned include financing for cars, after market warranties and links to third parties such as insurance companies.

Description: VGATrader.com - VGATrader.com is a peer-to-peer video card trading web site.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: VGATrader.com is a peer-to-peer video card trading web site. Registered users can use our service as a meeting place and exchange PC video cards with each other. Listed PC Video Cards will often carry a lower price compared to the same card offered through a regular online hardware store. In many cases the savings will be substantial.  Here is how the process works: * Sellers place the video card classifieds in a predefined category that corresponds to type of the graphics hardware they want to sell. * Buyers browse for available VGA cards and buy them directly from sellers. * Sellers and buyers negotiate payment and shipping directly with each other using our web service as a meeting place.  Finally, at the end of the transaction both sellers and buyers can exchange feedback and end the transaction.  VGATrader.com is a free service. We do not charge any kind of listing fees. Instead we rely on non intrusive Google's text ads service — adsense and PayPal donations for the revenue. The overall experience that we are aiming for is a combination of the EBay:registered: like interface + free Craigslist:registered: elements + some of the formalized aspects of forums trading. We are trying to blend all 3 of those into a single package and hopefully not only appeal to the community of PC hardware enthusiasts, but also to new people that are confused about the available choices of video cards.

Description: WOW is a non-profit association supporting web professionals and educators, offering industry standard certification exams.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: WebProfessionals.org, also known as the World Organization of Webmasters, is a non-profit professional association that supports practicing professionals and those who teach them. The organization works with experts within industry, education, and government to create a series of vendor-neutral industry standard certification exams. It also provides a platform for members to login, interact, and celebrate their achievements through annual awards. The organization is dedicated to the support of individuals and organizations in the web professional field.
